                    "body": "My suspicion would be that pa.total_allocated_bytes would be 0 (as @pitrou said, we are not using the Arrow memory pools here) and that remaining 500MB is fragmented data leftover in the system allocator.\r\n\r\nThat being said, it does beg the question why the system allocator isn't able to release the memory.  In other words, what's making up the fragments occupying those pages?  I'd guess it's some kind of python thing but it could possibly be some kind of global.  It's also maybe possible that the system allocator just doesn't try that hard to return data pages to the OS.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
